---
title: Sweet-As-Honey Chicken with Green Beans over Jasmine Rice
description: We all have a soft spot for the sticky-sweet chicken that’s a staple of takeout dinners. But it’s not exactly a meal for any night of the week—until now. We’re swapping out the heavy glaze for a fresh burst of ginger and a swirl of honey and soy sauce. Served with tender green beans on a bed of jasmine rice, it’ll give you a good reason to toss out the phone number for your delivery joint.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sweet-as-honey-chicken-959d60ad.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-as-honey-chicken-5d2f8ec77ac6d400086d304d-cc853d69.pdf
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-as-honey-chicken-5d2f8ec77ac6d400086d304d
servings: 2
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 570 kcal
  fat: 16 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 60 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 520 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

In a small #pot, combine @water{3/4%cup} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil. Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce (except green beans). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Cut @lime{1} into wedges. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 TBSP.

Once water is boiling, add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} to pot. Cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve. Meanwhile, pat @chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-low heat. Add garlic and minced ginger. Cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Add @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} and let cook until almost evaporated.

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @honey{4%teaspoon}, half the @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, and @water{2%TBSP} into pan. Simmer until mixture is thick and glossy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; return chicken to pan and turn to coat in glaze.

Pierce green bean bag with a #fork; place bag on a #plate. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully transfer to a #medium bowl and toss with @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Squeeze in lime juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between plates. Top with @green beans{6%ounce}, chicken, and any remaining glaze. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.